Let $BD = 2x$ and $CD = 5x$.  Then $BC = 7x$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, C, D;

B = (0,0);
C = (7,0);
A = (0,10);
D = foot(A,B,C);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--D);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$10$", (A + B)/2, W);
label("$17$", (A + C)/2, NE);
label("$2x$", (B + D)/2, S);
label("$5x$", (C + D)/2, S);
[/asy]

By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $ABD$,
\[AD^2 = AB^2 - BD^2 = 10^2 - (2x)^2 = 100 - 4x^2.\]By the Pythagorean Theorem on right triangle $ACD$,
\[AD^2 = AC^2 - CD^2 = 17^2 - (5x)^2 = 289 - 25x^2.\]Hence, $100 - 4x^2 = 289 - 25x^2$, so $21x^2 = 189$.  Then $x^2 = 9$, so $x = 3$.  Therefore, $AD^2 = 100 - 4x^2 = 100 - 36 = 64$, so $AD = \boxed{8}$.

